Key Match Events: Leweling scored the only goal in the 64th minute.
Rudiger received a yellow card in the 63rd minute.
Schlotterbeck and Anton received yellow cards in the 90+3rd minute.
Reijnders received a yellow card in the 30th minute.
Wieffer received a yellow card in the 63rd minute.
Simons received a yellow card in the 90+3rd minute.
Pre-Game Insights: The match is part of the UEFA Nations League and takes place at Allianz Arena.
Both Germany and Netherlands are unbeaten at the halfway stage and look set to progress to the quarter-finals.
Germany's only dropped points so far came in the reverse fixture last month.
Germany has never reached the finals of the Nations League but has only suffered one defeat on home soil in the competition.
Germany has only won two of the previous eight meetings against the Netherlands.
The Dutch are aiming to reach the finals for the third time in four editions.
Virgil van Dijk's red card in the previous match against Hungary means he will not be available for this match.
Germany's Marc-Andre ter Stegen is out for the season due to injury.
Jamal Musiala and Kai Havertz are also unavailable for Germany due to injuries.
Niclas Fullkrug has had a difficult start at West Ham United.
Tim Kleindienst and Jonathan Burkardt were handed debuts against Bosnia.
Undav has scored eight goals in eight games since netting in the reverse game last month.
Matthijs de Ligt is likely to start at the back for the Netherlands due to Van Dijk's suspension.
The Dutch are short on options at left-back and in the center of the park due to injuries.
